pseudo-classe: specifies a special state
pseudo-element: lets you style a specific part

div, p Selects all <div> elements and all <p> elements
div p Selects all <p> elements inside <div> elements
div > p Selects all <p> elements where the parent is a <div> element
p ~ ul	Selects every <ul> element that are preceded by a <p> element among all children of p
div + p	Selects all <p> elements that are placed immediately after <div> elements
[target[^$*]=_blank] Selects all elements with target="_blank" ([] : start, end, substring)

p:not(.intro)
li:nth-child(3)
li:nth-last-child(n)
ul:nth-of-type(n)
li:only-of-type
li:first-of-type
